channel.title: RuneCrafting Gfx & Model
channel.description:
You must have done yaranova's TuT on how to add gfx's to a client on rune~server.
Step1:Download the model from here http://uppit.com/CNCZO2 ,Click save to disk and then go to your desktop and drag the zip into your models folder.
Step2:Run your client and type: add model 9933 , after that it will say model added sucesfully.Now close down the client and the server and compile both of them.
Step3:Open up your class 23.java and add this case under another one :
[code]case 646: // This is the GFX ID originalDataID = 602; //makes it spin gfx.anInt405 = 9933; // This is the Model ID! (Original was 19069) break; [/code] After you are done that look for int newSpotAnimCount = ; in your class23 (on top of the case's) and add a number on it so if it was int newSpotAnimCount = 1; change it to int newSpotAnimCount = 2;.
Step4:Save your class23.java and compile here is the command if you want to test it out:
[code]if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("runecrafting")) { stillgfxz(646, absY, absX, 0, 50); //makes the gfx appear }[/code]
Video Here: http://img532.imageshack.us/flvplayer.swf?f=Tmovieun4
Credits To Me D D 3 and Jagex And Squal707 for inspiring me to work on clients. I will be adding more TuT's and probably all of the gfx TuT's.
